Celebrities have a lesser known side to their lives, usually reserved for intimate friends and family... (from the Introduction)

{HISTORY}

Did you ever want to cook alongside Lucille Ball or drink a glass of bourbon with Dean Martin? How about breakfast with Jackie Kennedy or a barbecue with Frank Sinatra? Here's your chance...

In this very fun vintage 1960s era cookbook, American actor and singer Dinah Shore gathered up 62 of her best Hollywood friends and asked them to submit a recipe for a fundraiser for the volunteer group Women For. The result is this Celebrity Cookbook, a fabulously fun collection of 65 recipes that covers first courses, entrees and desserts.

Laid out in equally fun fashion, each page is stylishly unique with recipe contributions written on personal letterhead, company stationary, and some even written in their own handwriting. Besides famous actors, recipes were also submitted by are well known politicians and authors of the day, giving readers and home cooks an intimate look into the kitchens of the 1960's celebrity set.

{SPECIAL FEATURES}

- 65 recipes submitted by 62 1960's era celebrities

- 93 pages

- Recipes include simple classics like homemade waffles, Beef Stroganoff and Boston Cream Pie; interesting arrangements like Red Flannel Hash, Meat Balls in Wine Sauce, Portuguese Fish Chowder and Permission Cake, to the exotic Meat Stuffed Prunes, Spiced Pigs Feet and Caviar in Aspic

- Published by Price Stern Sloan, 1966

{CONDITION}

In beautiful vintage condition. All pages and coverboards are clean and bright. The spine is tight and all pages intact. There is a little bit of minor bumping to the corners on the spine side of the coverboards. There is a gift inscription from a previous owner written in marker on the inside front end paper. Please see photos.

{SIZE}

Measures 5.75" inches (width) x 9.75" inches (length) x .5" inches (thickness)

